    "department": "Legal",
    "description": "ABOUT SUNO\n\nWe're building the world's first platform for creating and discovering original music, including Suno Studio, a generative audio workstation, and Hooks, a new way to create and share videos that bring songs to life.\n\nPowered by the leading music-creation model and designed to amplify imagination, our platform makes it possible for anyone to turn inspiration into music. With Suno, ideas flow into sound, songs become yours, and everyone can experience the joy of creating.\n\n\nSuno is one of the fastest-growing AI startups in the world, backed by leading investors including Menlo Ventures, Lightspeed Venture Partners, Matrix, NVentures, and Hallwood Media.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nWe’re looking for a leader to build our legal operations and strategy function from the ground up. You’ll own the systems and processes that let a small, high-impact legal team scale with one of the fastest-growing companies in AI: contract management, outside counsel coordination, legal tech stack, the workflows that connect legal to every corner of Suno, and cross-functional strategy.\n\nThis is a high-autonomy role that rewards initiative and creative problem-solving. You’ll report to Suno’s General Counsel and work alongside a tight-knit legal team covering legal \u0026 business affairs, commercial, litigation, product \u0026 privacy, and corporate matters. The measure of success is simple: our most important business initiatives stay unblocked, well-supported, and ahead of the curve.\n\nCheck out our Suno version of the job here! https://suno.com/s/VJDKZxpMx6K8WeaW\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO\n\n - Select, implement, and manage Suno’s legal technology stack—contract lifecycle management (CLM), matter management, e-billing, and AI-powered legal tools that match the way we build.\n\n - Own the end-to-end contract lifecycle from intake and triage through execution and renewal, building scalable processes, templates, and self-service tools that empower the business to move quickly.\n\n - Manage relationships with outside counsel and legal service providers, including budget tracking, performance evaluation, and strategic allocation of work.\n\n - Build and maintain KPI dashboards to track legal team performance, spend, and turnaround times—giving leadership clear visibility into how legal operates.\n\n - Partner cross-functionally with Finance, People Ops, and business teams to ensure legal processes and strategy align with how Suno actually works, not how legal departments traditionally work.\n\n - Develop and refine legal department infrastructure: playbooks, knowledge management, onboarding materials, and the operational backbone that lets a lean team punch above its weight.\n\n\nWHAT WE’RE LOOKING FOR\n\nMust-haves:\n\n - 8+ years of experience in operations, with at least some time spent in legal operations specifically.\n\n - Proven track record of building or scaling legal operations functions from early stages — you’ve done the zero-to-one work before.\n\n - Expertise in legal technology, including CLM platforms (e.g., Ironclad, DocuSign CLM, Agiloft), e-billing systems, and matter management tools.\n\n - Strong analytical skills and a data-driven mindset—you build dashboards, not just spreadsheets.\n\n - Excellent project management instincts, with the ability to run multiple initiatives simultaneously without dropping threads.\n\nNice-to-haves (we encourage you to apply even if you don’t check every box):\n\n - Experience at a high-growth technology or AI company navigating ambiguity and rapid change.\n\n - Familiarity with AI-powered legal tools and emerging legal tech—bonus points if you’ve built workflows around them.\n\n - Background in contract management, paralegal work, or legal practice.\n\n - CLOC certification or equivalent legal operations training.\n\n - Experience managing outside counsel in complex IP, regulatory, or litigation-heavy environments.\n\n\nPERKS \u0026 BENEFITS FOR FULL-TIME EMPLOYEES\n\n - Company Equity Package\n\n - 401(k) with 3% Employer Match \u0026 Roth 401(k)\n\n - Medical, Dental, \u0026 Vision Insurance (PPO w/ HSA \u0026 FSA options)\n\n - 11 Paid Holidays + Unlimited PTO \u0026 Sick Time\n\n - 16 Weeks of Paid Parental Leave\n\n - Creative Education Stipend\n\n - Generous Commuter Allowance\n\n - In-Office Lunch\n\n\nWHY THIS ROLE IS SPECIAL\n\nMost legal ops roles ask you to optimize existing systems. This one asks you to build them. You'll join a legal team at the ground floor and have the rare opportunity to implement processes that will scale with us as we grow. Your fingerprints will be on everything we build.\n\n\nADDITIONAL NOTES:\n\n - Applicants must be eligible to work in the US\n\n - This role requires working on site in our Los Angeles or San Francisco office\n\nSuno is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer. We consider qualified applicants without regard to race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, marital or family status, disability, genetic information, veteran status, or any other legally protected basis under provincial, federal, state, and local laws, regulations, or ordinances. We will also consider qualified applicants with criminal histories in a manner consistent with the requirements of state and local laws, including the Massachusetts Fair Chance in Employment Act, NYC Fair Chance Act, LA City Fair Chance Ordinance, and San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
